    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/vv40-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions) is accepted under a risk-informed argument that static compression-bending is the dominant failure mode for non-cannulated pedicle screws and that the single test condition covers the primary regulatory QoIs. The validation activity — characterised in the evidence package as an observational-study data compilation from two independent laboratories operating under ASTM F1717 SOPs — is treated by the assessment team as functionally equivalent to a controlled experiment given the standardised fixture constraints. The FEA ensemble demonstrates consistent agreement with bench data (all E/uval < 1.96; all percent differences < 10%). Overall credibility is assessed as sufficient to support a Medium assurance level for the stated COU.",
